1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,880
 Let's pray. Father, we just thank you so much for Susanna Glenn, the kids, for the mantle of authority that is placed upon Susanna here at the Vine,

2
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:16,480
 her pastoral gift to teach and to share out of what you've done in her life.

3
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:21,440
 Lord, we open up our hearts to all that you have to say to us today through Psalm 27.

4
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,480
 We thank you for this in Jesus' name. Amen.

5
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:31,920
 Good morning. I get the privilege of continuing this series on waiting,

6
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:36,960
 and today we're looking at the gift of waiting, pursuit and presence.

7
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:43,200
 And we're going to continue to explore Psalm 27, and we're going to focus in on verses four to six

8
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:52,400
 today. "One thing I ask from the Lord, this only do I seek, that I may dwell in the house of the Lord

9
00:00:53,920 --> 00:01:00,000
 all the days of my life, to gaze on the beauty of the Lord and to seek him in his temple.

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:08,880
 For in the day of trouble he will keep me safe in his dwelling. He will hide me in the shelter

11
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:17,920
 of his sacred tent and set me high upon a rock. Then my head will be exalted above the enemies

12
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:24,640
 who surround me at his sacred tent. I will sacrifice with shouts of joy. I will sing

13
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:34,480
 and make music to the Lord. Three weeks ago a friend of mine invited me to a float experience.

14
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:43,760
 You enter a large," you can see up here a picture of it, "you enter a large domed futuristic capsule

15
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:51,520
 which is filled with warm water that has an extremely high concentration of epsom salts

16
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:59,600
 diluted in it. The pod has a lid, you enter, you lie down, you shut the lid,

17
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:08,080
 and when you lay down you are very buoyant because of the epsom salts that are diluted in the water.

18
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:17,280
 And then you float for an hour in complete darkness and quiet."

19
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:22,080
 Some of you who are claustrophobic are going, "Oh, I can't think of anything else."

20
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:29,120
 There's nothing to distract you, there's nothing to do but wait.

21
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:37,120
 And so knowing I was going to speak today on the topic of waiting, I started a conversation with

22
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:49,360
 God and I said, "What's the deal with waiting? Why is it so important?" I feel like I'm a true

23
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:55,040
 Hong Konger now having said those questions. What's the deal with waiting? Why is it so important?

24
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:59,600
 This is what I heard in response to my questions.

25
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,720
 We wait for what we value.

26
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:16,880
 We pursue what we value. Andrew said in week one that in this world no one likes to wait.

27
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:25,680
 So when we do choose to wait, to actively lean in, it's for something we truly value.

28
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:32,720
 God reminded me of a recent moment after church, my family and I,

29
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:37,840
 we went to Samson Restaurant. We wanted to have Thai food for lunch.

30
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:46,320
 But when we got there, there was a big, you know what it is, right? A big queue, a big line.

31
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:54,720
 Because it has incredible Thai food and everybody knows it. We joined the line and we started

32
00:03:54,720 --> 00:04:04,560
 waiting, anticipating the yummy food that we would have. But after a few minutes of not moving at all

33
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:13,040
 and looking at the long stretch of people in front of us, we decided to leave.

34
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:19,040
 We crossed the road, we entered a building, we went up a flight of stairs

35
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:27,280
 and we went into another Thai restaurant. There was no wait. There was plenty of tables.

36
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:33,360
 And very soon we had food on the table and we were eating. However,

37
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:44,640
 there was a price to us not waiting. I've eaten the food of Samson's before and I can tell you

38
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:51,600
 it is really good. And I've now eaten the food of this other Thai place.

39
00:04:51,600 --> 00:05:00,240
 And the food was nowhere near as good. It filled us up, but it was nowhere near as good.

40
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:07,360
 And God said to me, "Susanna, when you lose sight of the value of something, you stop waiting.

41
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:17,680
 And you start to pursue quicker alternative substitutes. Alternative routes even that are not

42
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:27,200
 as good. You settle for lesser versions." Andrew spoke to us recently about how many of us had

43
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:33,440
 created lesser versions of Jesus. You know, the Jesus that kind of fits with our worldview,

44
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:36,960
 that makes us feel comfortable and doesn't challenge us to change.

45
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:46,640
 This is what happens when we don't wait on Jesus. Lying in that pod, I felt convicted that I had

46
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:57,280
 lost sight of the value of Jesus. Lost sight of the value of actively slowing down and waiting.

47
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:08,160
 And by losing sight of the value of waiting for Jesus, my life was being filled up with substitutes.

48
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:13,040
 I was pursuing lesser things.

49
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:21,440
 God gave me a taste in that pod of what it's like when we truly wait.

50
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:31,920
 He reminded me of my worth. He realigned my identity to match how he saw me.

51
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:35,920
 He encouraged me to believe in the more.

52
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:41,680
 You see, when we have a lesser version of Jesus,

53
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:49,440
 we get contained because it's like we put him in this box that we can handle.

54
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:59,200
 And what also gets contained is your creativity, your belief, your understanding of what he's

55
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:06,640
 capable of doing. And the real Jesus that I encountered in the waiting in that pod,

56
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:10,320
 he blew out the edges of my dreaming.

57
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:25,680
 And anticipation for the future was reignited in me. Waiting is for our benefit. Psalm 103,14

58
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:35,280
 says, "For he knows our frame. He remembers that we are dust." God compassionately understands us.

59
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:39,920
 He created us. He understands our limitations and our frailties.

60
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:50,480
 This verse, "He remembers that we are dust." It makes me smile because dust gets everywhere.

61
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:57,200
 It flies off in every direction. It swirls. It clings to things it shouldn't.

62
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:03,440
 Have you ever run your finger across something in your home and gone, "How did dust get here?"

63
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:10,160
 It makes me smile because it's such an accurate depiction of us.

64
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:16,240
 Yes, God made us from the dust, but the way we live in this modern world with our scattered

65
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:25,520
 thoughts, our constant movement, our distractions, our connection and clinging to things that we

66
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:32,960
 shouldn't. God knows this about us and he whispers, "Be still."

67
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:44,800
 "Be still and know me." Stop rushing and pursuing lesser things.

68
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:54,720
 The waiting is for our benefit. The first thing that waiting does is realign us to the one

69
00:08:55,920 --> 00:09:06,000
 thing that's needed. "One thing I ask from the Lord," David says, "This only do I seek,

70
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:11,280
 that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life

71
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:21,520
 to gaze on the beauty of the Lord, to seek him." We wait for and pursue the things we value.

72
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:28,880
 Does the value we carry in our hearts for God's presence match David's in this verse?

73
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:33,440
 What are you willing to wait for?

74
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:46,800
 As I was thinking about this, I remembered my husband. Every time one of my children or I travel

75
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:54,320
 overseas, he always comes and he waits at the airport to pick us up. Every time.

76
00:09:54,320 --> 00:10:02,960
 No exception. Doesn't matter if we come in on a midnight flight, six in the morning, he's there.

77
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:13,040
 And it made me realize he values us. He wants us to know that we're important to him.

78
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:25,840
 We wait for what we value. Just have a look at these verses. Psalm 27, 14, "Wait for the Lord,

79
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:35,920
 be strong. Let your heart take courage. Wait for the Lord." Lamentations 3, 25, "The Lord is good

80
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:47,280
 to those who wait for him, to the soul who seeks him." Isaiah 30, 18, "Therefore the Lord waits to

81
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:55,760
 be gracious to you. Therefore he exalts himself to show mercy to you. For the Lord is a God of

82
00:10:55,760 --> 00:11:06,720
 justice and blessed are all those who wait for him." Isaiah 64, 4, "From of old no one has heard

83
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:17,120
 or perceived by the ear. No, I has seen a God besides you who acts for those who wait for him."

84
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:23,200
 Do we value God enough to wait?

85
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:32,160
 Andrew has said in a previous sermon that waiting is not passive. It's active.

86
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:36,400
 Waiting is an active process of preparation.

87
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:44,160
 The second thing that waiting does is it strengthens our resolve for future challenges

88
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:50,160
 by deepening our awareness and intimacy with the one who shares the waiting with us.

89
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,800
 Listen to these verses of David again. "One thing I ask from the Lord, this only do I seek,

90
00:11:56,800 --> 00:12:02,880
 that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life, to gaze on the beauty of the Lord,

91
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:11,840
 to seek him in his temple. For in the day of trouble he will keep me safe.

92
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:22,400
 He will keep me safe. He will hide me and set me high upon a rock."

93
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:30,400
 Waiting, actively seeking God's presence, spending time in the temple, prepares David for the day

94
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:39,520
 of trouble. The waiting actively prepares David. The waiting time teaches him that he can hope

95
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:49,920
 in God's timing and his safety. David is able to anticipate and speak confidently that when the day

96
00:12:49,920 --> 00:13:00,480
 of trouble comes, he declares that he can trust God. He declares he will not be alone. He declares

97
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:07,600
 that the God he's experienced in the waiting, he will keep me safe. He will hide me. He will set me

98
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:16,480
 high. Waiting gives us the answers we need for future challenges. It teaches us to trust in

99
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:25,440
 God's timing and prepares us for the uncharted and the unknown. Many years ago my family was living

100
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:33,840
 in Darwin, Australia. I was working as a substitute teacher and also working for a Christian NGO that

101
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:41,440
 was working into China. And we began to feel challenged that we were meant to relocate to Hong

102
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:50,720
 Kong to deepen our work with this NGO. At the time we had four young kids and we didn't have

103
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:59,920
 enough resources to transition our entire family overseas. Nevertheless, we began to speak and share

104
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:09,200
 as if we were going. A miracle happened when someone we hardly knew heard of our story.

105
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:13,600
 And when I say we hardly knew him, I'm not exaggerating.

106
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:23,280
 My husband has this gift and I see it in him all the time. He notices people on the fringes.

107
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:28,480
 Do you know what I mean? The people on the edges who don't quite fit in.

108
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:35,040
 And the church we were going to in Darwin, he noticed a young man who used to slip in

109
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:46,160
 sort of late and slip out early. And so my husband tracked him down and invited him for coffee.

110
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:54,400
 And in that sharing, this man asked what we were doing and Glenn shared, "Oh, we're planning to go

111
00:14:54,400 --> 00:15:03,520
 to Hong Kong. We want to work for this Christian NGO." And this young man said to Glenn, "Oh,

112
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:09,440
 give me your banking details. I'd like to give you something towards that." So Glenn did.

113
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:15,440
 The next day I remember Glenn rushing to me and saying, "Babe, look at this."

114
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:20,480
 And he showed me on the computer our bank balance.

115
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:26,720
 And this young man had deposited 25,000 Australian dollars into our bank account.

116
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:36,720
 So we packed up from Darwin. We travelled back to Queensland. Queensland is where we are from.

117
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:42,320
 And we were planning to go there to say our goodbyes to families, to wrap up loose ends

118
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:53,920
 and wait for our visas. And we began to wait. And we waited. And we waited some more.

119
00:15:53,920 --> 00:16:04,720
 And we kept on waiting. We had four kids. I was trying to homeschool them.

120
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:09,520
 Yeah, all you kids, all you people with kids are going, "Ooh."

121
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:20,400
 We were moving every few weeks from this parent's home to that parent's home. And when I say that,

122
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:26,960
 there's four hours between those parents' home of travel. We were going to people's farms.

123
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:32,000
 We slept on mattresses on concrete floors.

124
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:41,760
 Weeks turned into months. I remember it got to eight months and there was still no sign of visas.

125
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:49,680
 It's at moments like this in the waiting that we can struggle to feel God's presence.

126
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:56,640
 And the wait can make us feel like he's distant or maybe even absent.

127
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:06,560
 And these moments offer us a choice. Do we lean in or do we lean out?

128
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:16,400
 And I chose to lean in. I remember going into the downstairs bathroom of my parents' house,

129
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:21,360
 shutting the door. When you have kids, you know that this is one of the few places

130
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:29,520
 you can go to to escape. And I remember silently screaming out my frustrations to God,

131
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:39,280
 wrestling with him. "If you've called us, why? Why are we experiencing this? How long, God?"

132
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,120
 "How long?"

133
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:50,320
 And I remember saying to him, "I can't take this anymore. You're going to have to do something."

134
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:57,200
 I remember that the next week the visas came through.

135
00:17:57,200 --> 00:18:05,440
 We were able to book our tickets and come. I don't know all the reasons for the waiting,

136
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:10,560
 but I can tell you that God's timing was perfect.

137
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:20,720
 Our landlords, they came and picked us up from the airport. I don't know what Hong Kong landlords do,

138
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:31,840
 but it's rare, very rare. They came in a little green minivan and they picked us all up.

139
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:38,800
 They took us to the house. They had set up the house so that we had enough furniture and

140
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:43,520
 appliances so that we could start living in it straight away without having to race out

141
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:48,800
 to shops and get things. And they had included toys for the kids.

142
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:58,160
 Later on, we were to discover that they attended a Seventh-day Adventist church.

143
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:06,960
 And God had, just when they had heard our story, because we had met through this random Craigslist,

144
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:11,680
 they'd put their house on Craigslist at the time, it was so weird, but Glenn had found it.

145
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:17,840
 And, you know, they'd asked why we were coming and we shared and they said when they heard it,

146
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:21,120
 they just knew. They had to be a part of our story.

147
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:28,400
 I guess because of all the transition the children had experienced in those eight months,

148
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:33,360
 the constant movement, they immediately settled.

149
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:40,720
 They immediately were at peace in our new home. I can't describe it.

150
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:43,280
 It was just like they'd lived there forever.

151
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:49,360
 And our five-year-old, who'd been waking every night since she'd been born,

152
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:57,360
 waking us multiple times and getting up to all sorts of mischief in the night,

153
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:04,320
 she slept through from her first night in Hong Kong and she never woke again through the night.

154
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:09,600
 The waiting prepares you in ways you don't even know you need.

155
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:14,320
 The waiting forces you to trust if you let it.

156
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:18,240
 And in the day of trouble, you know,

157
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:23,440
 you intimately know the one who is alongside you and fighting for you.

158
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,920
 But what about the waiting that doesn't end?

159
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:31,120
 Come on, let's be real today.

160
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:36,960
 What about the spouse that never materialises?

161
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:41,200
 What about the child that never comes?

162
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:45,760
 What about the one you love never finding Jesus?

163
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:49,360
 Or the one you love never regaining?

164
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,160
 Or the one you love never regaining their faith?

165
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:58,320
 What about the change that you long for?

166
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:02,640
 The healing that you need, not happening?

167
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:06,400
 What about this type of waiting?

168
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:12,720
 We're not talking about days or weeks, we're talking about years and decades.

169
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:21,680
 This type of waiting, there are not sufficient words to describe the ache that builds within you.

170
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:26,480
 And this is what this series has revealed to me.

171
00:21:26,480 --> 00:21:31,440
 Andrew taught us that in God's eyes, waiting is a gift.

172
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,020
 A gift.

173
00:21:34,020 --> 00:21:39,440
 How can this type of waiting be a gift?

174
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:43,760
 He also taught us about kavah, the Hebrew word for waiting,

175
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:47,520
 to bind together, to gather together, to look, to expect.

176
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:51,360
 God's type of waiting calls us to

177
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:57,280
 remember all the promises and the hopes and the dreams and in them and through them,

178
00:21:57,280 --> 00:22:01,520
 begin a process of anticipating all the good that is to come.

179
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,520
 Hoping and expecting it'll come to pass.

180
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:10,720
 And God spoke to me in the night through my dreaming moments

181
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:15,600
 and showed me that I was no longer anticipating my future.

182
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:22,880
 The waiting, the longing, the ache in one area of my life,

183
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,360
 I no longer anticipated any change.

184
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:33,360
 I don't think I'm the only one in the room who is experiencing long-term waiting.

185
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:39,280
 I don't think I'm the only one here whose anticipation has died.

186
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:47,360
 Anticipation in the waiting for hopes, promises, dreams to come to pass, for change to come.

187
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:53,840
 You know when you examine your heart today that the length of the wait has crushed all expectation.

188
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:58,800
 You no longer eagerly anticipate God's intervention.

189
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:06,960
 The Bible says that hope deferred makes the heart sick.

190
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:13,040
 There have been many times over the course of the last 12 years that I've been waiting

191
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:18,160
 in one particular area of my life that I know my heart has been sick.

192
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:23,920
 This type of waiting will challenge you to your core.

193
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:30,480
 It will strip you bare, leave you feeling incredibly vulnerable.

194
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:34,080
 It'll cause you to question your faith.

195
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:39,440
 And if you're not careful, it'll cause you to abandon it.

196
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:43,440
 It can numb you,

197
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:50,160
 rob you of your joy, your sense of hope, and your dreaming for change and a better future.

198
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:55,200
 I don't have all the answers for this type of waiting.

199
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,160
 I'm still waiting.

200
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:02,720
 I'm still waiting.

201
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:13,200
 But I do know there are some things that I do know I have not been left alone in the waiting.

202
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:22,000
 I do know that I've come to experience deeper levels of God's comfort than I ever have before.

203
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:26,160
 I do know that I have a rich trust

204
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:30,400
 that I never would have had except for this journey.

205
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:34,000
 God has revealed himself time and time again

206
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:41,360
 in the waiting, speaking words of comfort, reminding me of his nearness,

207
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:46,640
 and challenging me and calling on me to deepen my trust.

208
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:54,800
 I know I can give greater measures of love and grace away

209
00:24:56,800 --> 00:25:00,320
 because I've experienced the depths of God's infinite grace.

210
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:07,520
 That picture in Ezekiel 47 where a man is led deeper and deeper into the water

211
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:11,760
 that is streaming from the temple, that picture of God's presence.

212
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:17,120
 The man gets led to a point where it is so deep,

213
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:23,360
 the only way he could possibly experience it is if he was to swim.

214
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:30,080
 This type of waiting where the answer does not come and the change has not happened,

215
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:33,040
 this type of waiting has taught me to swim.

216
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:40,320
 To have nothing to rely on to keep me up but the water, the presence of God.

217
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:48,080
 However, this doesn't just happen. You have a choice to make.

218
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:54,800
 In these times of waiting, you can choose to lean in,

219
00:25:54,800 --> 00:26:05,600
 to learn to trust God afresh and begin to anticipate afresh the future that he has for you.

220
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:15,840
 Or you can lean out, you can pull away and you can settle for substitutes.

221
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:24,800
 The third thing waiting does is remind us of his promises and heighten our gratitude.

222
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:33,760
 "Then my head will be exalted above the enemies who surround me. At his sacred tent I will

223
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:40,640
 sacrifice with shouts of joy. I will sing and make music to the Lord." When David sings this,

224
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:48,080
 he has not yet been delivered from his enemies. He is still surrounded but as he waits,

225
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:55,440
 he gets a glimpse of the good that is to come. He has the faith to declare that he will be

226
00:26:55,440 --> 00:27:01,520
 delivered from his enemies. His heart is filled with gratitude and joy as he's reminded of God's

227
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:09,360
 enduring presence and protection. In the midst of the waiting, even before his release from his

228
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:18,320
 enemies, David breaks forth in shouts of joy, singing and praising God. Some of us today need

229
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:25,920
 to prophetically shout for joy and express our gratitude to God. Not because the answer has come,

230
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:31,360
 not because the waiting has ended, but because we believe in the one

231
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:33,360
 who is walking with us through the waiting.

232
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:48,560
 Waiting is for our benefit. God doesn't need it. He is ever present. But we take time.

233
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:55,600
 We take time for our minds to declutter and all the thoughts that are swirling around to settle.

234
00:27:55,600 --> 00:28:03,760
 Waiting, it realigns us to the one, the one thing that's needed.

235
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:08,080
 Waiting strengthens our resolve for future challenges.

236
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:14,240
 And waiting reminds us of his promises and heightens our gratitude.

237
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:24,800
 Today we need to rediscover and truly value God's presence. We wait for what we value.

238
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:34,400
 So how do we begin this process? How do we restore our value that we hold in God?

239
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:41,760
 We start by removing the lesser things, the substitutes that have crowded our life and our

240
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:49,760
 mind and our hearts, stolen our time and causes to drift away from what God truly intended for us.

241
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:55,840
 I'm wearing a pair of Converse today, see?

242
00:28:55,840 --> 00:29:01,920
 I bought them in Japan when my husband and I were there for our 30th wedding anniversary.

243
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:12,000
 I really, really wanted them. But this store, I wanted a size seven.

244
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 They only had six and a half in the style that I wanted. And I didn't want to wait.

245
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:27,200
 So I bought them. And every time I wear them,

246
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:37,440
 I'm aware that I should have waited. My toes get a little bit pinched.

247
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:42,000
 And while we're in worship, I was like, I think the circulation is getting cut off.

248
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:54,640
 I share this with you, because if I hadn't told you, you wouldn't know.

249
00:29:56,240 --> 00:30:00,640
 These shoes are like substitutes. They aren't the ones that I should have had.

250
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:04,320
 They aren't the ones that would have been the right fit for me.

251
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:11,600
 And many of us in here today, you've settled for substitutes. You've settled for lesser things.

252
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:19,600
 People looking at the outside of your life might not know. But you do.

253
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:26,000
 You do. It was like whenever I went out with somebody that I knew my parents,

254
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:30,640
 you know, didn't want me to go on out with, and they weren't a Christian, I would know.

255
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:34,880
 I'd feel it. It's not quite the right fit.

256
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:44,480
 So how do we, how do we respond to this? We have to remove the lesser things.

257
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:52,400
 I want us all to personally choose to create space here today to realign ourselves

258
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,960
 to the one thing that's needed.

259
00:30:54,960 --> 00:31:05,680
 If you're sitting here today and you know that you've taken paths that you shouldn't,

260
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:12,800
 that you've become impatient maybe in the waiting and have settled for a substitute

261
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:18,560
 or something lesser than what God intended for you, we're going to take some time now.

262
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:24,640
 We're going to close our eyes. And if that's you, I want you to open up your hands to be

263
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:32,720
 honest with God and say, "I want to begin the process of letting go of the lesser things,

264
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:41,520
 the things that have taken up my time and my energy and the paths I've walked that have not been

265
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:43,760
 the paths that I should have walked."

266
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:54,000
 Father, we open up our hands before you and we are all aware that at times we settle for substitutes.

267
00:31:54,000 --> 00:32:05,680
 We lose sight of the value of waiting for your intervention, waiting for you to bring the right fit,

268
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:12,640
 the right plans, the right person, the right job.

269
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:23,440
 And so we settle for substitutes. We settle for things that you never intended for us.

270
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:29,680
 So Father, right now we open up our hands as a sign to you that we're willing to let them go.

271
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:36,480
 We're willing to surrender them.

272
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:46,400
 And Father, we pray right now that our value, the value we hold in our hearts of waiting on you,

273
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:50,640
 Father, we want to restore that today.

274
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:59,280
 We remind ourselves that those who wait, your word says they will be blessed.

275
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:08,000
 We remind ourselves today that your word says that when we wait, you act on our behalf.

276
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:20,560
 Father, thank you.

277
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:28,400
 Thank you for your goodness and your gentleness and your kindness.

278
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:32,320
 Thank you for your goodness and your kindness that you wrap us up today.

279
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:43,200
 I'd also now like to pray for those who have been waiting a long time.

280
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:50,960
 You've been waiting a long time for something and when I shared

281
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:58,480
 that God had revealed to me that I had stopped anticipating my future, you understood that.

282
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:08,000
 You were sitting there thinking, "Yeah, I can't see a good future. I can't see where

283
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:14,240
 change could possibly come from. I've lost all hope in God stepping in."

284
00:34:18,080 --> 00:34:20,960
 If that's you today, I'd like you to open up your hands.

285
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:37,040
 Father, the waiting is painful, God.

286
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:42,960
 But we remember today that we're not alone

287
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:48,800
 and that you understand our pain, you understand our frame,

288
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:55,200
 you're familiar with all our ways. You are not distant, you are in this.

289
00:34:55,200 --> 00:35:04,080
 So, Father, I pray right now for the ache and the pain that you would come and wrap us up

290
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:11,360
 in your tender love, that we would have ears right now to hear your gentle whispers,

291
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:15,680
 that you would speak clearly to us,

292
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:27,280
 that you would give us the courage to deepen our trust, that the waiting is for our benefit

293
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:31,520
 and that good things can happen even in the middle of the waiting.

294
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:47,040
 And lastly, we're going to stand in a minute and we're going to take an opportunity to declare

295
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:54,880
 prophetically. Some of you today, you need to declare prophetically

296
00:35:54,880 --> 00:36:02,640
 that you are going to trust the one who holds your future in his hands. You're going to trust

297
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:08,560
 that he is the God of the impossible, even when you can't see how anything could happen or change

298
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:12,640
 or be different. You're going to declare it prophetically, that you believe he's able,

299
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:19,760
 that he can do things that are beyond your understanding and that you are going to trust him.

300
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:25,200
 I did this on the way to work this week and I began to declare to God that

301
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:34,160
 he is the God who can do things that I can't even imagine, that where my limitations were,

302
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:39,440
 I chose to prophetically declare that I wasn't going to let my limitations prevent me from

303
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:46,400
 believing and hoping and dreaming and trusting. Today we're going to do that together.

304
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:53,760
 We're going to sing a song together that declares that. So would you stand with me?

305
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,160
 [Music]

306
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:22,320
 There's something powerful in declaring together as a community.

307
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:30,560
 I just encourage you to reach out to someone, to hold someone's hand right now.

308
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:36,720
 So maybe put your arm on someone's shoulder to link up across the auditorium.

309
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:45,760
 As we sing, we declare, we're going to pray first. We're going to do it together.

310
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:48,080
 [Music]

311
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:54,080
 Father, we declare prophetically right now that you are the God that does not change,

312
00:37:54,080 --> 00:38:00,960
 that what you've done in the past, you can do today. And where we have lost our faith,

313
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:06,960
 where we've lost our anticipation for a better future, for the good future you promised us,

314
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:14,400
 where we've lost that God, restore right now in your powerful name. We declare you are still able.

315
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:21,120
 We declare that you can move mountains. We declare, Father, that you can restore relationships.

316
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:28,560
 We declare, God, that the ones who are lost can be found. So, Father, we lift up our faith together

317
00:38:28,560 --> 00:38:34,240
 and we prophetically declare that you are the God of the waiting, that you are in it with us,

318
00:38:34,240 --> 00:38:41,840
 and we will trust you. We will trust you that we will see all the promises fulfilled, God,

319
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:47,840
 that you will meet us in the waiting, that you will bless us in the waiting, that you will cause

320
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:59,680
 us to be a blessing to others in the waiting. We declare that right now in your precious holy name.

